                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner take the handkerchief from the prosecutor's pocket - he had it in his hand, and was putting it into his left-hand pocket; the moment I took him he dropped it.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. There was a man selling stuff to cure corns and worts; a young man there stood talking to me, and the gentleman went by with his handkerchief hanging out of his pocket - I took it to give him, and this gentleman took me.</p>
               <p>The prisoner received a good character.</p>
